HEADWORD: Creationism
<hw>Cre*a"tion*ism</hw> <pr>(-?z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
doctrine that a soul is specially created for each human being as soon
as it is formed in the womb; -- opposed to
<xex>traducianism</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

